                  By this rule it ſhall be (hoſtia) an hoſt, when it is not a Sacrifice; and a reſerued hoſt is no Sacrifice, howſoeuer conſecrated. And what if a mouſe, or other vermin,Io▪ de Burg 4. partis c. 8. de Miniſtratione Euch. Salmer. Tom. 8. Tract. 29. An Euchar. ſit proprie ſacrificium ſhould eat the Hoſt (it is a caſe put by themſelues) who then ſacrificeth? To ſtop all mouthes; Laicks eat as well as the Prieſt, there is no difference in their manducation, but Laicks ſacrifice not; And (as Salmeron vrges)

